The musical is a religious satire on Mormonism, also known as the Church of Latter-Day Saints, with songs like 'Making Things Up Again' and 'All-American Prophet', as well as containing a character called 'F*** Frog' and one scene with a singing clitoris.

It garnered both praise from critics and an impressive haul of theatre awards in the U.S., including numerous Tony Awards and a Grammy.

Nobody at the London Temple of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints was available for comment.

